    "comment_count": 9,
    "description": "This PR is an attempt to fix a few small bugs that I and other users have found, improve memory usage (only by a bit, however), and broaden support for different software packages. \r\n\r\n1. Support a wider variety of instrumental response files (detect the FITS unit which has the response matrix instead of assuming the name). \r\n2. More intelligent determination of the energy bounds when writing a spectrum.\r\n3. Fixed two small bugs in `_convolve_with_rmf`: a precision-related bug that occurs in NumPy 1.9 and later when summing the weights, and the end of the iteration over the energy range was off by 1. \r\n4. Lazy-evaluate the sky coordinates in an `EventList`. This results in a modest memory improvement. \r\n5. Write FITS files with more information so that external tools (like CIAO and FTOOLS) can read them and manipulate them more easily. For the latter, I had to add `astropy.time` to the on-demand import. \r\n",
